67471d641233ef7b1f36eae0.In the past five years, briefly describe:
My housing journey has been a bit of a classic San Francisco tale. I initially landed in a somewhat cramped but charming studio in the Inner Sunset five years ago. It was a rental, and while I loved being close to Golden Gate Park and the vibrant Irving Street, the lack of space started to feel restrictive as my needs grew. The rent was also, predictably, quite high and seemed to creep up a little each year.
About three years ago, I decided to look for something a bit bigger and, perhaps, slightly more affordable I ended up moving to a one-bedroom apartment in the Outer Sunset. It was further from the main action, but the apartment was significantly larger, and having more space was a real plus.
